{"data":{"featured":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Modeling Receiver Ability Bayesianly","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/joshallen.github.io/static/bc07ff3690a98cb746be03df6fa60032/89684/rfm.png","srcSet":"/joshallen.github.io/static/bc07ff3690a98cb746be03df6fa60032/dc90d/rfm.png 175w,\n/joshallen.github.io/static/bc07ff3690a98cb746be03df6fa60032/c2b9a/rfm.png 350w,\n/joshallen.github.io/static/bc07ff3690a98cb746be03df6fa60032/89684/rfm.png 700w","sizes":"(min-width: 700px) 700px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/joshallen.github.io/static/bc07ff3690a98cb746be03df6fa60032/bf026/rfm.avif 175w,\n/joshallen.github.io/static/bc07ff3690a98cb746be03df6fa60032/53a94/rfm.avif 350w,\n/joshallen.github.io/static/bc07ff3690a98cb746be03df6fa60032/3f7ae/rfm.avif 700w","type":"image/avif","sizes":"(min-width: 700px) 700px, 100vw"},{"srcSet":"/joshallen.github.io/static/bc07ff3690a98cb746be03df6fa60032/48048/rfm.webp 175w,\n/joshallen.github.io/static/bc07ff3690a98cb746be03df6fa60032/d8098/rfm.webp 350w,\n/joshallen.github.io/static/bc07ff3690a98cb746be03df6fa60032/c73ff/rfm.webp 700w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 700px) 700px, 100vw"}]},"width":700,"height":500.00000000000006}}},"tech":["PyMC","Polars","ggplot","matplotlib"],"github":"https://github.com/joshuafayallen/joshuafayallen.github.io/blob/main/blog/2025/passing-td-factor-model/polished-final-model.py","external":"https://joshuafayallen.github.io/blog/2025/passing-td-factor-model/","cta":null},"html":"<p>Isolating a player's skill from their surroundings is quite difficult since their are a variety potentially confounding team level variables. I built a Bayesian Hierarchical Factor model to estimate latent ability of every NFL pass catcher from 2002-present controlling for these team level factors and use Hilbert-Space Gaussian processes to capture in season time dynamics and career aging curves.</p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"NFL Power Rankings","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/png;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/joshallen.github.io/static/05c2043145197b79b11149a49647c35e/da56b/demo.png","srcSet":"/joshallen.github.io/static/05c2043145197b79b11149a49647c35e/29e34/demo.png 175w,\n/joshallen.github.io/static/05c2043145197b79b11149a49647c35e/27866/demo.png 350w,\n/joshallen.github.io/static/05c2043145197b79b11149a49647c35e/da56b/demo.png 700w,\n/joshallen.github.io/static/05c2043145197b79b11149a49647c35e/3f188/demo.png 1400w","sizes":"(min-width: 700px) 700px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/joshallen.github.io/static/05c2043145197b79b11149a49647c35e/40567/demo.avif 175w,\n/joshallen.github.io/static/05c2043145197b79b11149a49647c35e/5e660/demo.avif 350w,\n/joshallen.github.io/static/05c2043145197b79b11149a49647c35e/0ead3/demo.avif 700w,\n/joshallen.github.io/static/05c2043145197b79b11149a49647c35e/81bb5/demo.avif 1400w","type":"image/avif","sizes":"(min-width: 700px) 700px, 100vw"},{"srcSet":"/joshallen.github.io/static/05c2043145197b79b11149a49647c35e/1dac5/demo.webp 175w,\n/joshallen.github.io/static/05c2043145197b79b11149a49647c35e/4d0bf/demo.webp 350w,\n/joshallen.github.io/static/05c2043145197b79b11149a49647c35e/80410/demo.webp 700w,\n/joshallen.github.io/static/05c2043145197b79b11149a49647c35e/67fff/demo.webp 1400w","type":"image/webp","sizes":"(min-width: 700px) 700px, 100vw"}]},"width":700,"height":455.99999999999994}}},"tech":["React","FastAPI","D3.js","PyMC","Polars"],"github":"https://github.com/joshuafayallen/Fantasy-Football-Project/tree/main/rankings","external":"https://fantasy-football-project-psi.vercel.app/","cta":null},"html":"<p>Who is the best team in the NFL? This is one of the most hotly debated topics throughout the NFL season. One of the big reasons this is so difficult is that not every team plays eachother. I alleviate these concerns by building a Bayesian paired-comparision model to answer these questions. You can see all these rankings by navigating to the webapp.</p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"The NFL MMM","cover":null,"tech":["PyMC","Polars","matplot","ggplot"],"github":null,"external":"https://joshuafayallen.github.io/blog/2025/nfl-marketing/","cta":""},"html":"<p>What personnel groupings lead to explosive plays? Teams have a finite amount of plays to dedicate to various personnel groupings. They are further constrained by the players they have available, game script, and the strengths of their opponents. To answer this question I turn to the marketing literature to answer this question.</p>"}}]}}}